<title>UK: Ford Motor Credit ups 5-yr bond to $1.25 bln.</title>
<headline>Ford Motor Credit ups 5-yr bond to $1.25 bln.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following bond, announced earlier by joint lead managers Goldman Sachs and Salomon Brothers, has been increased by $250 million.</p>
<p> BORROWER   FORD MOTOR CREDIT CORP</p>
<p> AMT    $1.25 BLN     COUPON     **	  MATURITY    28.FEB.02</p>
<p> TYPE	 STRAIGHT  ISS PRICE  **	  PAY DATE    28.FEB.97</p>
<p> FULL FEES  35 BP     REOFFER    **	  SPREAD	+38-39 BP</p>
<p> MOODY	A1	  LISTING    LUX/HK/SI</p>
<p> S&amp;P	  A+	  DENOMS (K) ONE     SALE LIMITS US/UK/SI/HK</p>
<p> NEG PLG    YES	 CRS DEFLT  NO	  FORCE MAJ   YES</p>
<p> GOV LAW    NEW YORK  HOME CTRY  U.S.	TAX PROVS   STANDARD</p>
<p> MGT/UND    10 BP     SELL CONC  25 BP</p>
<p>UNDERLYING GOVT BOND WHEN-ISSUED FIVE-YEAR U.S. TREASURY -- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7658</p>
